Jiggle Da JORKLE

The team with the most historical wins, plays as the trivia host first.
    *If the teams are tied, then the trivia host is determined randomly

Team A = Trivia Host
Team B = Guessers

At the start of the game Team B has 1 minute to look at the JORKLE SPUNK SCRIPTURE to review any rules.

Team A then has 1 minute and 22 seconds to create a trivia question based on the contents of the JORKLE SPUNK SCRIPTURE and to write a hint on a piece of paper to give players.

Team A's Goal is to get one member of the opposing team to answer their question correctly while having no other member of the opposing team guess correctly.
    *Each member of Team A gets 1 point for achieving this Goal.

After Team A asks their question, Team B chooses one of the following within 33 seconds:
    *Team B may not communicate in any way after the question is asked. Each player must write their answer on a piece of paper to not give their answer away.

    Guess the answer correctly on the first try and gain 2 points.
        or
    Use the hint and guess correctly to gain 1 point.
*Players who answer wrong take 1 drink. Players get no points if they are the only who to answer correctly.

Teams switch sides are repeat until the 20 minute timer is up. The team with the most points at the end of the timer wins the sub-phase. Each member of the team is awarded with 5 Zoinks.

Overtime: If there is a tie, then the games continue until a team takes the lead and a winner is determined.